headline: Stocks dip as government shutdown continues, rare earths rally: What to watch this week
summary: The stock market will enter the second full week of the government shutdown. Investors will also focus on big bank earnings.

headline: Is It Time to Reevaluate Progressive After Its Recent Share Price Dip in 2025?
summary: Are you eyeing Progressive and wondering whether now is the moment to buy, sell, or simply watch? If you feel caught between FOMO and fear, you are definitely not alone. Progressive's share price has cooled slightly in the short term, dipping 2.3% over the last week and 3.3% in the past month. However, those relatively modest declines follow a staggering rally, with shares still up 113.3% over the past three years and 174.4% in five. Clearly, the long-term trend has rewarded patient...
